.TH MPI_Group_range_incl 3 "6/24/2006" "LAM/MPI 7.1.4" "LAM/MPI"
.SH NAME
MPI_Group_range_incl \-  Creates a new group from ranges of ranks in an  existing group 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
#include <mpi.h>
int MPI_Group_range_incl(MPI_Group g, int n, 
                       int ranges[][3], MPI_Group *png)
.fi
.SH INPUT PARAMETERS
.PD 0
.TP
.B g 
- group (handle) 
.PD 1
.PD 0
.TP
.B n 
- number of triplets in array  
.I ranges
(integer) 
.PD 1
.PD 0
.TP
.B ranges 
- a one-dimensional array of integer triplets, of the 
form (first rank, last rank, stride) indicating ranks in
.I g
or processes to be included in 
.I png

.PD 1

.SH OUTPUT PARAMETER
.PD 0
.TP
.B png 
- new group derived from above, in the order defined by 
.I ranges
(handle)
.PD 1

.SH NOTE

When a group is no longer being used, it should be freed with
.I MPI_Group_free
\&.


